OL,3,CWhat happens next in the election of a
OL,4,Cnew First Minister in Wales?
OL,6,FUnder the Senedd's standing orders,
OL,7,Fthe Llywydd or Presiding Officer, Elin
OL,8,FJones, must invite nominations. If
OL,9,Fthere's only one nomination, then she
OL,10,Fdeclares that person to be the
OL,11,FSenedd's nominee for the post of First
OL,12,FMinister.JIf there's more than one
OL,13,Fnomination - in other words, if the
OL,14,FWelsh Conservatives and Plaid Cymru
OL,15,Fnominate their leaders - then there
OL,16,Fhas to be a kind of vote, a roll call.
OL,17,FThe Llywydd will call each member in
OL,18,Falphabetical order to vote for a
OL,19,Fcandidate. She and the Deputy
OL,20,FPresiding Officer, Labour's David Rees
OL,21,Fare excluded from this vote.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/5
