OL,3,CWhat happens next in the election of a
OL,4,Cnew First Minister in Wales?
OL,6,FIf two members are nominated, the
OL,7,Fcandidate with the most votes becomes
OL,8,Fthe nominee. If they have the same
OL,9,Fnumber of votes, there has to be
OL,10,Fanother roll call.JThis is exactly
OL,11,Fwhat happened in 2016 when members of
OL,12,FPlaid Cymru, the Conservatives and
OL,13,FUKIP voted for Leanne Wood to become
OL,14,FFirst Minister instead of Carwyn
OL,15,FJones.JBetween them they had 29 votes
OL,16,Fas did Labour with the support of the
OL,17,FLiberal Democrat Kirsty Williams.
OL,18,FTalks were held and another vote the
OL,19,Ffollowing week led to Carwyn Jones
OL,20,Fresuming the post of First Minister.
OL,21,FThis time around, even if the
OL,22,Fopposition parties were to unite they
OL,23,Fcan't block Labour's nomination
OL,24,Fbecause one of their members, Rhys ab
OL,25,FOwen, has been suspended from the
OL,26,FSenedd, so Labour can muster 29 votes
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/5
