OL,3,CWhat happens next in the election of a
OL,4,Cnew First Minister in Wales?
OL,6,FIn this event, a simple majority of
OL,7,FLabour votes will mean that the Labour
OL,8,Fleader wins. In the highly unlikely
OL,9,Fscenario of them not winning a
OL,10,Fmajority, the candidate with the least
OL,11,Fvotes is eliminated and another roll
OL,12,Fcall held.JOnce all this is over, the
OL,13,FLlywdd sends a letter to the King (by
OL,14,Ffax!) telling him the name of the
OL,15,FSenedd's nominee to become First
OL,16,FMinister.JThe King then appoints that
OL,17,Fperson First Minister by Royal Warrant
OL,18,Fand when that has been granted the new
OL,19,FFirst Minister will swear his oath to
OL,20,Fthe monarch in a ceremony in Cardiff.
OL,21,FAfter that happens, the new First
OL,22,FMinister will begin assembling his
OL,23,Fcabinet before taking his first
OL,24,FQuestion session in the Senedd on the
OL,25,F16th April following the Easter recess.
